
Replacing SSL certificate for Mirror Registry for Red Hat OpenShift

https://access.redhat.com/solutions/6980268
========================================================
Phase 1: Generate a New Certificate on the Bastion Host
Since the mirror registry is using a local self-signed certificate, a new certificate must be generated using OpenSSL. The certificate should include the Subject Alternative Name (SAN) field to ensure compatibility with OpenShift 4.

Log in to the bastion host (bastion2025.lab.ocp.lan).

Create the OpenSSL configuration file:

cat <<EOF > quay-openssl.conf
[req]
distinguished_name = req_distinguished_name
x509_extensions = v3_req
prompt = no

[req_distinguished_name]
C = US
ST = VA
L = New York
O = Quay
CN = bastion2025.lab.ocp.lan

[v3_req]
subjectAltName = DNS:bastion2025.lab.ocp.lan, IP:72.1.1.17
EOF
Generate a new certificate and key (valid for 10 years):
openssl req -new -x509 -sha256 -nodes -days 3650 \
  -keyout local-quay.key \
  -out local-quay.crt \
  -config quay-openssl.conf \
  -extensions v3_req
Phase 2: Update the Mirror Registry
Apply the newly generated certificate to the mirror registry.

Run the following command to update the existing mirror registry configuration:
./mirror-registry install --init \
  --ssl-cert local-quay.crt \
  --ssl-key local-quay.key
Note: This command automatically updates the registry configuration and restarts the Quay containers.

Verify that the new certificate is being served:
openssl s_client -connect bastion2025.lab.ocp.lan:8443 | openssl x509 -noout -enddate
Phase 3: Update the OpenShift Clusters
After the registry certificate has been updated, each OpenShift cluster must be configured to trust the new certificate.

Create or update the trusted CA ConfigMap:
oc create configmap mirror-registry-ca -n openshift-config \
  --from-file=bastion2025.lab.ocp.lan..8443=local-quay.crt \
  --dry-run=client -o yaml | oc apply -f -
Configure the cluster to use the ConfigMap:
oc patch image.config.openshift.io/cluster --type=merge \
  -p '{"spec":{"additionalTrustedCA":{"name":"mirror-registry-ca"}}}'
Monitor the rollout and wait until all MachineConfigPools show UPDATED=True:
oc get machineconfigpool
The Machine Config Operator (MCO) will distribute the updated trust bundle to all nodes.

Once the above steps have been completed, please let us know the results. If you encounter any issues during the process, we will be happy to assist further.

One Small Suggestion to Add:
For the new cluster that the you are currently trying to create (the sno1 in the logs), you must also include the new local-quay.crt in install-config.yaml file under the additionalTrustBundle section before they start the installation. Otherwise, the new cluster will fail to pull the initial release images.

  Example for the customer's install-config.yaml:

   1 additionalTrustBundle: |
   2   -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
   3   <Contents of local-quay.crt>
   4   -----END CERTIFICATE-----
